OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F439A1717529014
OL,3,CControversial low traffic
OL,4,Cneighbourhood scheme to be scrapped
OL,6,F"In principle, who can object to LTNs?
OL,7,FBut the road to hell is paved with
OL,8,Fgood intentions, and we are certainly
OL,9,Fthere now. We did warn you about
OL,10,Funintended consequences, economically,
OL,11,Fsocially and politically. We should
OL,12,Fvote to scrap this divisive, harmful
OL,13,Fand unwanted scheme."
OL,15,FCllr Tracy Adams added: "I know not
OL,16,Feverybody will agree with the decision
OL,17,Fthat has been made today. I believe
OL,18,Fthis is a good compromise.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G5/7
